-- Chelsea’s Luiz Is Heading to Barcelona, Star Says: Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2013-06-03T09:46:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-03/chelsea-s-luiz-is-heading-to-barcelona-star-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the web.  Luiz Leaving  Chelsea’s Brazilian defender  David Luiz  will join Barcelona
for a 30 million-pound ($45.8 million) fee, the  Daily Star 
reported.  Jose Mourinho , who’s set to be confirmed as Chelsea coach
today, doesn’t see Luiz fitting in with his “regimented”
style, according to the Star.  Hammers Goalie  West Ham will sign Real Betis goalkeeper Adrian today,  the
Daily Mail  reported.  Adrian, 26, is likely to be an understudy to 38-year-old
Jussi Jaaskelainen at first, the Mail said.  Navas Move  Sevilla winger Jesus Navas is edging closer to a move to
Manchester City,  the Sun  reported.  The 27-year-old Spaniard may fetch a 25 million-pound fee,
according to the Sun.  Reina Replacement  Liverpool wants to hire Sunderland’s Belgian goalkeeper
Simon Mignolet if Pepe Reina leaves for Barcelona,  the Guardian 
reported.  Stoke’s Asmir Begovic and Reading’s Alex McCarthy are other
possible replacements, the Guardian said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Duff in  Madrid   at
 aduff4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
